1.title: Uncompahgre National Forest
1.plot: Colton and Jack head to the Colorado Rocky Mountains for an action-packed canyoneering adventure down a two hundred and seventy foot waterfall.

2.title: Return to the Colorado Rockies & Great Sand Dunes National Park
2.plot: Colton and Jack return to Colorado's Rocky Mountains to hit the dunes of Great Sand Dunes National Park. Along the way they recall their favorite adventures in Colorado including climbing their first 14er in San Juan National Forest, and whitewater rafting in Dinosaur National Monument.

3.title: Canyonlands National Park
3.plot: Jack and Colton hike in Utah's Canyonlands National Park exploring the true meaning of wilderness.

4.title: Crater Lake National Park
4.plot: Colton and Jack are biking around the deepest lake in Oregon's Crater Lake National Park. Their natural views include Wizard Island and the Pinnacles Overlook.

5.title: Return to Grand Teton National Park
5.plot: Colton and Jack return to Wyoming's Grand Teton National Park. Their adventure includes kayaking the Snake River. Along the way, they recall their previous visits to this park including alpine skiing and climbing the Grand Teton.

6.title: Return to Yellowstone National Park
6.plot: Colton and Jack are day-tripping through Yellowstone. During their adventure, they share their previous park visits including the geyser basins, Grand Canyon of the Yellowstone, and whitewater rafting.

7.title: Return to Glacier National Park
7.plot: Colton and Jack recall their previous trips to Montana's Glacier National Park. Their adventure includes hand cycling, Going to the Sun Road, and hiking to the continental divide. A forest fire forces them to rearrange their plans.

8.title: Arkansas the National State
8.plot: Colton and Jack explore Hot Springs National Park, Buffalo National River and Ouachita National Forest.

9.title: Best of the Power of Nature
9.plot: Colton and Jack reflect on the experiences that taught them about the power of nature.

10.title: Return to Maui
10.plot: Colton and Jack are back in Maui, Hawaii to snorkel a volcanic crater and swim with sea turtles.

11.title: Island of Hawaii
11.plot: Jack and Colton swim with Giant Manta Rays and then scuba dive backwater during the largest zoological migration on this planet.

12.title: Top 10 Bear Encounters
12.plot: Colton and Jack's most exciting and intimidating encounters with the biggest mammals in North America.

13.title: Top 10 Cave Adventures
13.plot: Colton and Jack explore the mysterious worlds below as they look back on their most memorable cave adventures.

14.title: Seoraksan National Park

1.title: Katmai: Where the Bears Are
1.plot: Hosts Jack Steward and Colton Smith get up close and personal with the massive brown bears of Katmai National Park in Alaska, home to the largest population of brown bears on the planet. The guys watch bears fish for salmon and dig for clams along the Pacific Coast and camp out in the back country surrounded by bears.

2.title: Glacier Bay: White Thunder
2.plot: Jack and Colton experience the awesome power of Mother Nature in Alaska as they kayak with whales and sea otters through Glacier Bay National Park, witness glaciers crashing into the sea and trek to get up close to a mammoth Glacier.

3.title: North Cascades: Life on the Edge
3.plot: Going off the beaten path takes on new meaning for Jack and Colton in the "American Alps" in North Cascades National Park in Washington, as they're pushed to the limit and forced to overcome fears in a quest to make the climb of their lives.

4.title: Olympic: Obstacles and Animals
4.plot: Mountain goats, marmots and spotted owls are just a few of the creatures that Jack and Colton meet face to face as they journey through Olympic National Park in Washington. From rainforest to rocky coast to the magnificent mountains, the guys discover why Olympic is really three parks in one.

5.title: Katmai: Journey to the Volcano
5.plot: Jack and Colton trudge through miles upon miles of volcanic ash and forge a treacherous river in search of one of the most powerful volcanoes on earth. Oh, and they are on constant alert for brown bears too.

6.title: Voyageurs: Living Off the Land
6.plot: Jack and Colton head into the northland of their home state of Minnesota to live like the Voyageurs did centuries ago. If they don't gather it or catch it, they don't eat as they paddle their way across these awesome interconnected lakes.

7.title: Glacier National Park: Rocky Mountain High
7.plot: Jack and Colton prepare for a possible encounter with grizzly bears as they head high into the Rockies and across the continental divide on their first back-packing adventure in Glacier National Park.

8.title: Glacier National Park: Bears, Big Horns & Glaciers
8.plot: The guys have a run-in with a bear and a showdown with big horn sheep as the hit the trails and the epic Going-to-the-Sun Road of Glacier National Park.

9.title: Shenandoah: Climbing Virginia Rocks
9.plot: Jack and Colton take on Old Rag, one of the most dangerous trails in Shenandoah National Park, then belay each other 110-feet straight up a rock cliff.

10.title: Mammoth Cave: All About the Bats
10.plot: The guys creep and crawl for miles through the underground of Mammoth Cave National Park in Kentucky, and help researchers capture wild bats to track a deadly disease.

11.title: Zion: Red Rock Canyons High and Narrow
11.plot: Jack and Colton trek miles though an icy cold river, then hold on for dear life while climbing one of Zion National Park's scariest trails.

12.title: Bryce Canyon: Horses, Hoodoos and Mud Water
12.plot: Jack and Colton saddle up and check out the land of hoodoos, then go back country camping... ultra-light with no tent. It's just them and the creatures of the canyon floor.

13.title: Yellowstone National Park: Hot Spots and Wildlife
13.plot: The guys learn about the supervolcano that lies deep beneath the park and check out the hot spots it creates. Then they track the parks elusive wolves and other awesome wildlife.

14.title: Yellowstone: Old Park, New Views
14.plot: Jack and Colton experience the power of the Yellowstone River at its own Grand Canyon, towering waterfalls, and white water rapids.

15.title: Sequoia: In the Land of Giants
15.plot: Jack and Colton trek through the land of giants in California's Sequoia National Park. Then it's a face-off with fear as they take on a 150-foot climb straight up a sheer granite rock wall.

16.title: Death Valley: Destination Desert
16.plot: Jack and Colton head to Death Valley National Park in search of one of the most scarce resources in the park... water.

17.title: Joshua Tree: The Climber's Paradise
17.plot: It's a rocky ride for Colton and Jack as they explore the Chasm of Doom and climb The Eye of the Cyclops in Joshua Tree National Park.

18.title: Haleakala: In the House of the Sun
18.plot: Colton and Jack are on the island of Maui checking out Haleakala National Park. They're flying high and riding low while exploring the house of the sun.

19.title: Hawai'i Volcanoes: Trekking Mauna Loa
19.plot: Jack and Colton are taking on Mauna Loa, the largest volcano on Earth, battling altitude sickness and the threat of severe weather along the way.

20.title: Everglades: Slough Slogging & Sea Kayaking
20.plot: Colton and Jack are slogging their way through the sloughs of Florida's Everglades National Park. Then it's a marathon kayak adventure out to one of the remote keys in the gulf coast.

21.title: Pictured Rocks: Sleds and Snow Beds
21.plot: The guys face off with Mother Nature in Michigan's Pictured Rocks National Lakeshore, spending a cold winter in a snow trench before taking on a 70-foot wall of ice for a climb like none they've done before.

22.title: Best of Wildlife
22.plot: Hosts Jack Steward and Colton Smith relive some of their best wildlife encounters in the nation's national parks.

23.title: Best of Eat, Drink, Sleep
23.plot: Camping in the national parks is always an interesting experience for Colton and Jack, especially when it comes to finding resources for food and water and a place to sleep.

24.title: Best of Wildlife: Bears
24.plot: From the remote wilds of Alaska to the high Rocky Mountains of Montana and Wyoming, there's one animal that draws people to the national parks. Today, Jack and Colton revisit some of their greatest bear encounters and experiences.

1.title: Cumberland: Island Animal Encounters
1.plot: The guys visit one of the last undeveloped beaches on the Atlantic coast. Cumberland Island National Seashore is home to tons of wildlife and Jack and Colton see it all from manatees to manta rays, and alligators to wild horses.

2.title: Dry Tortugas: Fort Finds and Deep Dives
2.plot: The watery world of Dry Tortugas National Park has Colton and Jack taking their exploration into the sea, diving deep to check one of the largest coral reefs in the world and the marine life that call it home, from stingrays, to goliath grouper and even nurse sharks.

3.title: Great Smoky: Big, Tiny & Slimy
3.plot: Jack and Colton head deep into the woods to learn about the amazing life of black bears, and then no stone goes unturned as they search for some of the tiniest inhabitants of the Great Smokies. Finally, it's a lung-busting hike to the top of a Smoky Mountain peak for a stunning view.

4.title: Padre Island: Keeping Up with the Kemp's Ridleys
4.plot: Colton and Jack hit the beach for a raucous wind surfing race. Then it's hush-hush in the hatching room where the guys see endangered Kemp's Ridley sea turtles emerge from their shells before making their own mad dash to the ocean.

5.title: Apostle Islands: Sunken Ships and Carved Caves
5.plot: Hosts Jack Steward and Colton Smith explore the iconic sea caves carved into the cliffs of Lake Superior BY both kayaks and below the surface in scuba gear. Plus they check out a 100 year-old shipwreck sunk by Superior's wrath.

6.title: Glacier National Park: Grizzly Bears and Rough Rapids
6.plot: Jungle Jack Hanna joins the guys on a story-filled hike through bear country. The guys get a good look at a grizzly and take on some of the roughest whitewater rapids they've ever experienced.

7.title: Aniakchak: Wicked Whitewater
7.plot: Remote wilderness takes on a whole new meaning as Colton and Jack take on the white-water ride of their lives in Alaska's Aniakchak National Monument.

8.title: Denali: What Lies Beneath
8.plot: Jack and Colton are in Denali National Park traversing a crevasse-laden glacier to take on their first Alaskan Peak!

9.title: Craters of the Moon
9.plot: Lava caves and cinder buttes are giving Jack and Colton a park experience like no other as they explore the strangest 75 square miles in North America, in Idaho.

10.title: Denali: The Big Five
10.plot: Colton and Jack are taking on Denali and hoping to spot all of the parks Big Five. Plus, they're spending some time with the Denali sled dogs and the pups in training.

11.title: Mount Rainier: Man Against Mountain
11.plot: Jack and Colton team with U.S. Secretary of the Interior Sally Jewell for hike up Mount Rainier.

12.title: Grand Teton: Climbing in Grand Exposure
12.plot: Jack and Colton are in Grand Teton National Park for the biggest challenge of their lives... climbing the Grand!

13.title: Rocky Mountain: Ridin' High
13.plot: Jack and Colton are checking out Colorado's Rocky Mountains the same way visitors have for centuries - by hoof and by foot. In addition, they face an unexpected challenge while rock climbing a rock formation called the Twin Owls.

14.title: Capitol Reef: Cliffs, Canyons and Culture
14.plot: The guys hit the cliffs and canyons of Capitol Reef National Park in Utah to explore the history of the first settlers who called the land home.

15.title: Acadia: Boulders and the Bay
15.plot: Colton and Jack head to Maine's Rocky Coast for a taste of Acadia National Park. Spotting seals and dolphins to Bald Eagles and Peregrine Falcons... it's an unforgettable wildlife adventure down east!

16.title: South Dakota: Road Trip
16.plot: Colton and Jack are road trippin' through South Dakota. After a stop in Custer State Park, they'll do their best not to get stuck in Jewel Cave or lost in Badlands National Park.

17.title: Big Bend: Bend But Don't Break
17.plot: Jack and Colton mess with Texas and Texas strikes back. Rattlesnakes, intense heat and the Rio Grande's Rock Slide give the guys all they can handle in the Lone Star State.

18.title: St. Croix: Into the Abyss
18.plot: Colton and Jack are on exploring the island of St. Croix both above and below the surface. After lighting up the night in a bioluminescent bay they head into another kind of darkness... a wall dive into the abyss.

19.title: Virgin Islands National Park
19.plot: Jack and Colton are in Virgin Islands National Park in St. John, USVI. After hiking through the islands history, they'll trade in sunshine for moonlight to take on their first night scuba dive.

20.title: Great Basin: Top to Bottom Extremes
20.plot: Nature itself and elevation really push the guys to their limits while trekking up the tallest peak in Nevada's Great Basin National Park. After that, it is all downhill and underground when they go on a wild caving mission for this park.

21.title: Yosemite: Uphills and Down Falls
21.plot: Colton and Jack are in for some ups and down while visiting Yosemite National Park in California. And they get their hands while learning about the parks efforts to reduce trash going to landfill.

22.title: Best of Wildlife Big and Small
22.plot: From grizzly bears and bison to salamanders and baby sea turtles, Jack and Colton come across all sizes of animals during their adventures. It's a look back at all the best of big and small wildlife in our national parks.

23.title: Best of Water Adventures
23.plot: Whether it's shooting rapids, diving deep, kayaking caves or climbing ice it's easy to get a little wet and wild in the national parks. Jack and Colton look back at some of the best water adventures.

24.title: Best of Extreme Landscapes
24.plot: The varied landscapes of the national parks push Jack and Colton to the limit as they look back at some of their greatest adventures.

25.title: Best of California National Parks
25.plot: Colton and Jack look back on their best adventures featuring California's national parks. Included: Whale-watching, surfing and the Chasm of Doom.

26.title: Yellowstone: Fire and Ice
26.plot: It is destination fire and ice as Jack and Colton head to Yellowstone National Park for a winter adventure in the Rockies.

1.title: Channel Islands National Park
1.plot: Jack and Colton are exploring Channel Islands National Park of the coast of California. After a scuba trip into the parks famous Kelp Forest, they kayak through sea caves, and spy on seals and sea lions at one of the largest rookeries in the world.

2.title: Black Canyon of the Gunnison National Park
2.plot: The guys are taking the plunge into one of the deepest, darkest canyons in the country. It's a rock scrambling, poison ivy filled, route finding trek to the bottom. Then they'll hit the gold medal waters of the Gunnison River to try their hand a fly-fishing.

3.title: Dinosaur National Monument
3.plot: Jack and Colton are exploring this parks prehistoric past, checking out one of the great quarry of dinosaur bones ever found. Then it's a nail-biting, hold on tight whitewater trip down the Green River that gives the guys more than they bargained for.

4.title: Theodore Roosevelt National Park
4.plot: Colton and Jack take a walk in the footsteps of America's 26th President, Theodore Roosevelt. They observe animals big and small from the large bison to the tiny prairie dogs while walking among petrified trees that are a million years old.

5.title: Denali: Gold, Bears & Bike Rides
5.plot: The guys return to Denali and experience the park in an entirely new way - exploring the Denali Park Road, on bike, at midnight. They also try their luck at panning for gold and then head deep into the back country to explore the Denali Wilderness.

6.title: Wrangell-St. Elias: Trekking Glaciers
6.plot: Jack and Colton are exploring the biggest national park in the U.S. This trip is all about the glaciers as they hike on them, crawl under them and climb into them.

7.title: Wrangell-St. Elias Backpacking the Wrangell Mountains
7.plot: The guys venture into the rugged wilderness of the largest National Park in the U.S. They navigate their way through bear country to reach a peak so remote, it doesn't have a name.

8.title: Carlsbad Caverns National Park
8.plot: Colton and Jack are exploring the deep underground of Carlsbad Caverns in New Mexico. They'll check out the famous Big Room and then do some wild caving where they get a bit more than they bargain for thanks to monsoon season.

9.title: Deschutes National Forest
9.plot: Jack and Colton are willing to help protect an endangered species in Oregon. In addition, they mountain bike down a volcano and ATV on old lava fields.

10.title: Gates of the Arctic National Park
10.plot: Colton and Jack visit the country's most northern national park. It's a wild trip into the Arctic Circle.

11.title: Mount St. Helen's National Volcanic Monument
11.plot: The guys are bushwhacking their way to a hidden waterfall, exploring the "subway" of an old lava tube all before making the ultimate climb up Mount St. Helens.

12.title: Lassen Volcanic National Park
12.plot: Jack and Colton are in Lassen Volcanic National Park California. They're doing a little geocaching before exploring the parks geo thermal features. Then they climb Lassen Peak.

13.title: Humboldt Toiyabe National Forest
13.plot: The guys are in the most remote down in the lower 48, Jarbidge, Nevada. After exploring the town, they'll take on the tallest peak in the Jarbidge Wilderness - the Matterhorn.

14.title: New Mexico & Texas Road Trip
14.plot: Jack and Colton are road tripping through Southern New Mexico and Texas. The trip includes a walk through White Sands, checking out the country's largest solar observatory and a hike to the highest peak in Texas.

15.title: Washington, D.C.
15.plot: Colton and Jack are exploring America's history in the nation's capital. They'll visit Fords Theater and get a behind the scenes look inside the Washington Monument.

16.title: Mojave National Preserve
16.plot: Jack and Colton take a wild trip to California's Mojave Desert where they check out the world's largest concentration of Joshua Trees and mountain bike to a lava tube.

17.title: Virginia: From Coasts to Cliffs
17.plot: From the Atlantic coast to the cliffs overlooking the famous Potomac River, Colton and Jack are finding adventure in Virginia.

18.title: Return to Death Valley
18.plot: The guys are heading back to Death Valley to check out the famous Racetrack Playa. Then they'll spend a couple of days hiking into the park's rugged backcountry.

19.title: Best of Island Adventures
19.plot: From the deep, dark abyss to the top of the largest active volcano on earth. Jack and Colton look back on their most epic island adventures on land and beneath the sea.

20.title: Best of Frozen Landscapes
20.plot: Whether it's snowmobiling, ice fishing, mountaineering or repelling into glaciers there are endless ways to have fun on snow and ice. Jack and Colton look back at some of the best winter adventures in the national parks.

21.title: Best of Coast to Coast
21.plot: Colton and Jack are looking back on some of their greatest coastal park adventures. Included: sea-kayaking in the Channel Islands, air-boating in the Everglades and scuba diving the sea caves of the Apostle Islands.

22.title: Best of Wildlife: Close Encounters
22.plot: The national parks are full of amazing wildlife and marine life. Colton and Jack and have had their fair share of run-ins. They're looking back on some of their most heart-pumping, most exciting and scariest close encounters.

23.title: Okinawa, Japan
23.plot: Jack and Colton are in Okinawa, Japan immersing themselves in nature and parks. When their trip takes an unexpected turn, the guys find themselves stepping out of their comfort zone in a completely new way.

24.title: Iriomote-Ishigaki National Park
24.plot: Colton and Jack are visiting the remote Iriomote-Ishigaki National Park in Okinawa, Japan. They'll snorkel rare coral and kayak mangroves all while keeping a lookout for some of the deadliest snakes around.

25.title: Mt. Baker Snoqualmie National Forest
25.plot: Jack and Colton are learning out to survive in a wilderness of Washington state. Skills they learn include making fire, edible plants, and building a shelter.

26.title: Grand Teton National Park
26.plot: Winter in the Tetons means avalanche danger. Colton and Jack are learning what they need to do to be safe before setting out on a backcountry camping and alpine skiing adventure.

1.title: New River Gorge National River
1.plot: Jack and Colton are exploring one of the oldest rivers in North America and one of the biggest bridges in the country. After that, they hit the crazy whitewater of the New River.

2.title: NYC: National Parks of New York Harbor
2.plot: Colton and Jack visit the parks of New York Harbor to learn about immigration and their own family history. Stops include Ellis Island and kayaking to the Statue of Liberty.

3.title: Biscayne National Park
3.plot: Jack and Colton check out the underwater world of Biscayne and help the park fight a dangerous invasive species.

4.title: Glacier: Back in Big Sky Country
4.plot: Colton and Jack are back in one of their favorite parks and bringing along their buddy, Joe Stone. Joe introduces them to a new way of biking Going-to-the-Sun Road and then it's a trip into the backcountry to camp.

5.title: Jasper National Park
5.plot: Jack and Colton travel through the heart of Alberta's Rocky Mountains while exploring the famous Icefields Parkway. In addition, they try a new adventure which involves canyoneering.

6.title: Churchill, Canada
6.plot: Colton and Jack head north to Manitoba, Canada hoping to spot their first ever polar bear in the wild. Then After a night of camping in a historic fort on Hudson Bay, they kayak with beluga whales.

7.title: Coconino National Forest
7.plot: Jack and Colton take on a section of the Arizona Trail as they bike-pack their way through ancient lava fields in the Coconino National Forest. They'll also explore a lava tube cave that's hundreds of thousands of years old.

8.title: Katmai: Return to the Valley of 10,000 Smokes
8.plot: Jack and Colton return to Katmai National Park in Alaska to find one of the last remaining known volcanic steam vents in the Valley of 10,000 Smokes.

9.title: Bears Ears National Monument
9.plot: Colton and Jack explore how Native American Tribes of the past lived in the vast, desolate high desert of Utah thousands of years ago. They'll route find their way to hidden ancient cliff dwellings deep in the canyons of Bears of Ears.

10.title: San Juan National Forest
10.plot: Colton and Jack are heading deep into the San Juan National Forest in Colorado to climb their first 14,000-foot mountain.

11.title: White Mountain National Forest
11.plot: Colton and Jack set out to hike the nine peaks of the Presidential Traverse in White Mountain National Forest in New Hampshire. It's a place known for the worst weather in the world, and this trip proves to be no exception.

12.title: Devils Tower National Monument
12.plot: Jack and Colton are in Wyoming to take on the biggest rock climb challenge of their lives - Devils Tower.

13.title: Santa Fe National Forest - Desert Survival
13.plot: Jack and Colton meet up with up with friend and Forest Ranger Rourke McDermott to learn the skills necessary to survive in the New Mexico desert.

14.title: Florida Parks: Hurricane Recovery
14.plot: Colton and Jack head back to Biscayne National Park and the Everglades to see the effects of hurricanes on the parks ecosystems and wildlife. They also lend a hand to help with debris clean-up.

15.title: Best of Caves
15.plot: Caves come in all shapes, sizes, and locations. Jack and Colton look back on their most epic cave adventures on the water, underground, and under ice.

16.title: Cayman Islands
16.plot: Jack and Colton are in the Cayman Islands to swim with stingrays and scuba dive a sunken Russian Frigate called the Captain Keith Tibbets. They also caving on the Island of Cayman Brac.

17.title: Jean LaFitte National Historic Park
17.plot: Colton and Jack head south to New Orleans, Louisiana to travel in the footsteps of well-known pirate turned patriot Jean Lafitte. Stops include: The French Quarter, Chalmette Battlefield and boating through the bayou of this national historic park.

18.title: Best of Rivers and Waterfalls
18.plot: From waterfall meditation in Japan to rafting Class V rapids in New River Gorge, Jack and Colton are looking back on waterfalls that challenged them, and rivers that earned their respect.

19.title: Best of Conservation
19.plot: Jack and Colton pitch in to protect the places we all love, and the creatures who live in them. Included: Endangered sea turtles of Padre Island, the bats of Mammoth Cave, and sorting visitor trash in Yellowstone.

20.title: Best of the Rockies
20.plot: Whether they're cycling up, hiking down, or canyoneering into the Rocky Mountains, Jack and Colton prove there are endless ways to explore the national parks, forests, and monuments of the Rockies.

21.title: Northern California
21.plot: Colton and Jack explore Northern California. Stops include Point Reyes National Seashore, the Golden Gate Bridge, and Alcatraz Island.

22.title: Grand Canyon National Park: Rim to Rim
22.plot: For the 100th episode of Rock the Park, Jack and Colton experience the Grand Canyon in a way less than 1% of visitors do: They're hiking rim-to-rim.

23.title: Denali: Dog Sledding
23.plot: Sophia Bush joins Colton and Jack as they temporarily return to Alaska's Denali National Park and Preserve. They participate in mushing dogs during their visit.

24.title: Santa Catalina Island
24.plot: Colton and Jack explore this island paradise off California's coast. They check out the island by bike, search for free-roaming American bison that inhabit the island and attempt their first solo shore dive.

25.title: Superior National Forest
25.plot: Jack and Colton are back in their home state to experience a true Minnesota winter. This adventure includes fat biking, and cross-country skiing to frozen waterfalls.

26.title: Nevada: The Loneliest Road in America
26.plot: Colton and Jack travel through U.S. Route 50 in Nevada and discover the state's natural history.

imdb.plot outline: ROCK THE PARK taps into America's love affair with our national parks. Our hosts, Jack Steward and Colton Smith, have made it their life's mission to explore every national park in this country. In the process, they come face to face with nature and push their physical limits as they go off the beaten path to discover some of the most awe-inspiring places on earth. The series is designed to inspire other Americans to seek adventure in the national parks.
imdb.title: Rock the Park
plot: The hosts take the audience to visit America's National parks as they get up close and personal with nature and explore the beauty of these national treasures.::Jwelch5742

In the process, they come face to face with nature and push their physical limits as they go off the beaten path to discover some of the most awe-inspiring places on earth. The series is designed to inspire other Americans to seek adventure in the national parks.::colleen needles steward

Host 'Jack Steward' (qv) joins 'Colton Smith' (qv) to travel to America's greatest treasures --the awe-inspiring national parks-- and to spotlight their beauty and wildlife. The series and its hosts tap into people's love affair with the widely varied natural preserves -- and remind Americans to hit the road and visit the sites for themselves.::Jwelch5742
